                  <!--saint-->
                
                  <residence/>
               <floruit> He was a medieval holy saint, a disciple of  
                  <persName ref="PRS9162TaklaHa">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName>Takla Hāymānot</persName>, who lived during the reigns 
                  of <persName ref="PRS10111WedemR">Wǝdǝm Raʿad</persName>, <persName ref="PRS1854Amdase">ʿAmda Ṣǝyon I</persName> and
                  <persName ref="PRS8595SayfaAr">Sayfa ʾArʿad</persName>. He is credited with the foundation of the monastery of  
                  <placeName ref="LOC2242DabraB">Dabra Bankʷal</placeName>, near <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum">ʾAksum</placeName> during the reign of King 
                  <persName ref="PRS8595SayfaAr">Sayfa ʾArʿad</persName>. It is also reported that King <persName ref="PRS8595SayfaAr">Sayfa ʾArʿad</persName> visited him and
                  richly endowned the monastery <placeName ref="LOC2242DabraB">Dabra Bankʷal</placeName> with lands in <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgray</placeName>
               </floruit>
